In this article, President Biden visits Arlington National Cemetery and reflects on the sacrifice of those who have served in the military. He mentions his son, Beau, who served in Iraq, and emphasizes that soldiers give their lives for their loved ones. When asked if the decision to go to war was difficult, Biden replies that it was clear to him. He states that the mission in Afghanistan was to eliminate Osama bin Laden and end the safe haven, not to unify the country. The article concludes with Biden expressing gratitude to those in attendance despite the rainy weather.